Design Problems to Fix
Navigation & UX
No bottom tab bar — the Files screen is buried behind "See all". Heavy users will never find it. A tab bar (Tools | Files | Settings) is standard for this category.
Arrow-based reordering (↑↓) — used in both Image-to-PDF and Merge. Drag-and-drop with react-native-draggable-flatlist is the expected pattern and already feels dated.
No PDF viewer — users can't preview what they're working with or review the output. They have to leave the app to open the file. This kills trust.
No haptic feedback — button taps feel dead. expo-haptics is a 2-line fix.
"FREE" badge in the header — signals Pro exists, but nothing is gated. Remove it or build the Pro tier.
Visual
Emoji icons instead of vector icons — @expo/vector-icons is already installed in package.json but never used. Emoji icons (🖼️ ✂️ 🔗) look unprofessional vs proper SVG icons.
No dark mode — expected in 2025. useColorScheme() + a dark palette would cover it.
Generic processing screen — same spinning progress bar for all 4 operations. Missed branding opportunity.
Critical Bug
Compress PDF doesn't actually compress — pdfOperations.js:223 just re-saves the PDF with useObjectStreams. For text-heavy PDFs the size won't drop. The "40-60% savings" claim shown in the UI is false and will generate 1-star reviews. A real compress needs image downsampling (not possible in pdf-lib alone — needs a different approach or a disclaimer).
