Revenue estimate: At 10,000 downloads, even 2% conversion to Pro at $14.99/year = ~$3,000/year. At 100k downloads with ads + Pro: could be $30-100k/year.

Easiest quick wins for revenue:

Add AdMob banner to HomeScreen and interstitial after each tool completes (3-5 days work)
Add a usage cap (3/day free) with "Upgrade to Pro" paywall (1 week work)
Submit to App Store / Play Store — you're not listed yet
Game-Changer Features (Ranked by Impact)
#1 — Camera Scan to PDF with Document Edge Detection
This is the single most searched PDF tool on mobile ("scan document to PDF"). Competitors like Adobe Scan and CamScanner built their entire businesses on it. You can do a basic version with expo-camera + manual cropping, or a premium version with ML Kit edge detection. This feature alone would double your downloads.

#2 — E-Signature
Draw, type, or upload a signature onto a PDF. Professionals (freelancers, lawyers, realtors) will pay for this. It works 100% offline with react-native-signature-canvas + pdf-lib placing the signature image. This is the easiest Pro feature to gate because users immediately see the value.

#3 — In-App PDF Viewer
Without viewing the output in-app, the product feels unfinished. react-native-pdf adds a full viewer. Pair this with annotation tools (highlight, draw) and you have a sticky daily-use app instead of a one-time utility.

#4 — PDF Annotation (Highlight / Notes)
Students and professionals annotate PDFs every day. If you own their workflow (annotate → share), they use the app daily. High retention = better App Store ranking = more organic downloads.


